                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14597331" author="frm" created="Tue, 23 Jun 2015 08:22:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2962&quot; title=&quot;SegmentNodeStoreService fails to handle empty strings in the OSGi configuration&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-2962&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-2962&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; can be used to implement a solution for this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14605710" author="frm" created="Mon, 29 Jun 2015 14:41:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=chetanm&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;chetanm&quot;&gt;chetanm&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=reschke&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;reschke&quot;&gt;reschke&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mreutegg&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mreutegg&quot;&gt;mreutegg&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;DocumentNodeStoreService&lt;/tt&gt; reads values from the framework properties first, and from the component properties next. The fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2962&quot; title=&quot;SegmentNodeStoreService fails to handle empty strings in the OSGi configuration&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-2962&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-2962&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, instead, implements the opposite solution because of how &lt;tt&gt;SegmentNodeStoreService&lt;/tt&gt; works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As asked on &lt;a href=&quot;http://markmail.org/message/5slapuge34tjdckx&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;oak-dev&lt;/a&gt;, do we have to maintain the current behaviour of the component? Can we make &lt;tt&gt;SegmentNodeStoreService&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;DocumentNodeStoreService&lt;/tt&gt; work the same?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14607920" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 30 Jun 2015 08:16:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know why the DocumentNodeStoreService reads first from framework properties. But I&apos;m in favour of unifying the resolution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14607928" author="frm" created="Tue, 30 Jun 2015 08:21:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=chetanm&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;chetanm&quot;&gt;chetanm&lt;/a&gt;, it&apos;s because of testing purposes (and it makes sense from this point of view). I will fix this issue by maintaining the same behaviour, but I opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3049&quot; title=&quot;Components should read OSGi configuration in a uniform manner&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-3049&quot;&gt;OAK-3049&lt;/a&gt; to track the progress on a unified solution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14611635" author="frm" created="Thu, 2 Jul 2015 08:05:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue can be solved if a new lookup strategy is added to &lt;tt&gt;OsgiUtil&lt;/tt&gt;. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3048&quot; title=&quot;Enable lookup of OSGi configuration from framework first and component next&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-3048&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-3048&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for further details.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14651712" author="frm" created="Mon, 3 Aug 2015 10:13:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch uses the new method introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3048&quot; title=&quot;Enable lookup of OSGi configuration from framework first and component next&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-3048&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-3048&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to handle empty strings in the OSGi configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14655092" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Wed, 5 Aug 2015 09:47:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;applied the patch with &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1694159&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1694159&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Francesco for the contribution!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14706667" author="edivad" created="Fri, 21 Aug 2015 12:13:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for 1.3.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
